Third-Party Licenses and Provenance

This document records third-party components and provenance information for the UNIX Version 4 experiment in the Kube-Archive project.

No UNIX source code, binaries, disk images, tapes, or ROMs are included in this repository.


---

SIMH Emulator

Project: SIMH

Source: https://github.com/simh/simh

License: MIT

Copyright: Copyright (c) 1993–2024 The SIMH Authors

SIMH is used to emulate historically accurate PDP-11 hardware required to run Research UNIX Version 4.


---

Debian GNU/Linux

Project: Debian GNU/Linux

Source: https://www.debian.org

License: Various (GPL, LGPL, MIT, BSD, and others)

Debian is used as the base operating system for the container image providing the runtime environment for SIMH.


---

Research UNIX Version 4 (Provenance)

Name: Research UNIX Version 4

Version: UNIX V4

Year: 1973

Original Author / Institution: AT&T Bell Laboratories

Original Hardware Platform: DEC PDP-11 (RK05 disk subsystem)

License Status: Proprietary (historical research use) © AT&T Bell Laboratories

Acquisition Source: User-supplied media obtained from legitimate archival or research collections (e.g., university archives, licensed historical UNIX distributions, or legally cleared research copies).

Accepted Media Formats:

RK05 disk images (e.g., .dsk)

PDP-11 compatible SIMH disk formats


Expected Runtime Path:

/data/unixv4.dsk

Notes:

This repository does not distribute UNIX V4 media in any form.

SIMH provides its own bootstrapping mechanisms and does not require proprietary ROMs.

Emulator configuration reflects historically accurate PDP-11 hardware appropriate for UNIX V4.

This experiment exists solely for educational, archival, and historical research purposes.



---

Legal and Ethical Notice

Users are responsible for ensuring that any UNIX V4 media they supply:

Was obtained from a lawful source

Is used in compliance with applicable licenses and institutional agreements

Is not redistributed in violation of copyright


This repository intentionally separates emulation infrastructure from copyrighted historical software artifacts.


---

Archival Intent

The UNIX-V4 experiment within Kube-Archive exists to:

Preserve historical computing environments using modern, reproducible tooling

Demonstrate containerized and Kubernetes-based execution of legacy systems

Maintain strict legal, ethical, and archival boundaries around proprietary historical software
